					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<b><i>Endgame</i></b><br>
						<i>1st-3rd December 2006</i><br>
						<br>
						Now is the moment of truth for Mordavia. If nothing can be done the land will soon be lost beneath the Swamp, and its people turned to mindless ghouls.
						You who struggle to save Mordavia have grasped the edges of the veil of darkness. Now you must find a way to undo that shadowy power or else, at last, be overcome. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_23.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 
			
			<br>
			<div class="largetitle">Past Events</div>

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_22.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/22.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Sanctuary</i></b><br>
						<i>22nd September 2006</i><br>
						<br>
						The city of Eranov can no longer feed its population. The Order of Erana have made plans to evacuate a portion of the population to the deep south of Mordavia.
						The intended destination is the elven land of Elendar, which has not yet been touched by the swamp. 
						Prince Brutus, half-elven son of the King of Mordavia and former lord of Eranov, has re-emerged and has announced that he is to be married. His royal wedding will take place in Elendar and news quickly spreads that all are invited and that there will be a celebration with food being distributed to anyone who attends. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_22.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_21.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/21.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>The Candle</i></b><br>
						<i>23rd August 2006</i><br>
						<br>
						Jurawicca had fallen to the Swamp. Eranov and its farmlands were surrounded by the mire. The elven noble Megilindir called a secret council of those who claimed to
						work against the Dark One, to meet in his inn the Gilthanas in Eranov. There they discussed what hope remains for the peoples of Mordavia.
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_21.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_20.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/20.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Winterspite</i></b><br>
						<i>8th July 2006</i><br>
						<br>
						After seizing the city of Eranov and being named Duke, the foreigner Lord Featherhall set about constructing dykes to protect the farmlands northeast of the city. 
						<br><br>
						The construction has reached Jurawicca, and an accord has been made with the elves. Now the city of Eranov calls for help to defend the dykes against the cultists who are threatening to destroy the dykes and let the Swamp enter.  
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_20.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_19.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/19.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Twilight in Eranov</i></b><br>
						<i>15th March 2006</i><br>
						<br>
						After years of battle, the small village of Berium in the heart of the Swamp has finally fallen. 
						The Staff of Erana has been removed, and the pestilent mire is closing in on the town. Only fortified Berium Keep 
						is safe from the ghouls and cultists roaming freely through the town.
						<br><br>
						The survivors of the last battle in Berium have escaped to Eranov, recalling there with a 
						rag-tag band of refugees and gypsies. They are staying at the Gilthanas Inn in the city. Berium has been deserted. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_19.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_18.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/18.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Reckonings</i></b><br>
						<i>17th-19th February 2006</i><br>
						<br>
						Heroes gathered in Berium to face the oncoming tide of the army of Nostralenia, brood of the Dark One. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_18.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
