				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_17.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/17.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>The Black Woods</i></b><br>
						<i>8th October 2005</i><br>
						<br>
						Count Eric von Braun harboured a bitter hatred for the robber baron Ghita Hammerhand. Long had the Count waited for an opportunity to strike out 
						against the man who has preyed on his people and even dared to invade the township of Dareen. Striking out with eight companions into the wild lands east of Dareen,
						the Count faced braved a cult of vampires in the swampy Black Woods before finally laying his foe to rest despite being taken in a devious ambush. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_17.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_16.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/16.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Conclave</i></b><br>
						<i>27th June 2005</i><br>
						<br>
						Lady Alia of the Order of Erana has called upon the priests of the Order of Erana to meet in conclave at the Temple of Erana in the city of Eranov, jewel of the northern principality. Also invited are all those who witnessed recent happenings in the town of Berium, for this assembly is to discuss those events and their implications.
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_16.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_15.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/15.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Solstice</i></b><br>
						<i>17th-19th June 2005</i><br>
						<br>
						The nights were longer, the days darker than any in these parts could remember. Now the Swamp crept inward too, closing like a hangman’s noose on the town of Berium.
						‘Ere eve of winter’s darkest night, when ancient superstition seized hold with an icy grip, there came a delegation that could spell ruin or bring salvation. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_15.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

