					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_13.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/13.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Meanwhile, Back In Faerie</i></b><br>
						<i>26 March 2005</i><br>
						<br>
						The Honourable Society of Key Wardens (the notorious Unseelie drinking club) is having its annual bash at the Lair of the Tunnel Web Spider.  It is renowned both for its interesting guests from all over Faerie and for the quality of its booze.  There might even be Royalty this year.  This is also their main recruiting drive and YOU have been invited.  Expect drinking, scheming, music and dancing. 
						<br><br>
						This event is taking place at the <a href="http://icon.sf.org.nz/">ICON Science Fiction Convention</a>, in Wellington.</a>
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_13.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_12.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/12.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>The Golden Bough</i></b><br>
						<i>13th March 2005</i><br>
						<br>
						All the people of the land have been issued a call to arms by the newly installed Baron of Berium, Glenn Underwood. He has ordered an open conference to be held in Berium, at which he hopes to speak with all the peoples of Mordavia regarding the Dark One, the newly formed Mages' Guild, and the state of the lands. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_12.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

