			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_11.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/11.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Death of a Merchant</i></b><br>
						<i>19th February 2005</i><br>
						<br>
						William Löwe was the owner of the "Eranov Exporters" guild house. He was a wealthy and widely travelled merchant, a purveyor of all kinds of goods. You knew him well. You were his family, his friends, his business colleages. Now he is dead. 
						<br><br>
						Death of a Merchant was a 1-hour Mordavia scenario that ran at BattleCry, starting at 1pm-ish on Saturday 19th February 2005.
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_11.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_10.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/10.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Ascension</i></b><br>
						<i>10th-12th December 2004</i><br>
						<br>
						Druidess and heroine, martyr and saviour, some hundred years have passed since Erana
						gave her life in defence of the Kingdom, which now celebrates her victory
						at the Feast of Erana. There gathered on that holy day in the town of Berium-in-the-Swamp, nobles and their attendants to contest the title of that small fiefdom
						where rests the fate of all the Kingdom of Mordavia. 
						<br><br>
						Valea Sarii fell to the ever-expanding Swamp, townsfolk battled minions of the Dark One in their dreams, the Staff of Erana was taken away from the town by the Order of Erana, 
						the Crux Palatinus was returned to the Paladin, and Berium's new lord of Baron Underwood was declared. 
						<br><br>
						<a href="event_10.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
						<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 


			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_09.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/9.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>The Thin Red Line</i></b><br>
						<i>24th October 2004</i><br>
<br>
There is a line protecting Mordavia from the desolation of utter chaos.  It is a line written in blood.  Join the Royal Guard.  Tell the stories of the brave few who protect their nation.
<br><br>
<a href="event_09.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_08.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/8.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>Shadow and Light</i></b><br>
						<i>19th September 2004</i><br>
<br>
Word has spread like wildfire of a wedding between the vampire Baron Eric von Braun, lord of Dareen and the demoness Gethsemane. Dareen, a northern forest village known for its sour faced villagers and occasional bandit attacks is the location of the wedding.
<br><br>
<a href="event_08.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 

			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_07.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/7.jpg" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>The Hollow Kingdom</i></b><br>
						<i>21st-23rd May 2004</i><br>
<br>
A land plagued by darkness is home to a new tragedy. Across the Kingdom is heard the weeping of mothers. Robbed of their children and their will to life, the land's workers slow to a halt, the merchants remain at home. The Great Depression has come. 
<br><br>
Deep in the clutching pinewoods, a young woman stumbles through patches of swamp. A party of soldiers follows some minutes behind. Night is falling. Beneath sickly stars she collapses in exhaustion, shielding the bundle strapped to her chest as she falls. The muffled sound of crying echoes through the bog, then quiets. In the dark the soldiers pass her by. 
<br><br>
<a href="event_07.htm">Click here for more information about this event</a>.
<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
			</div> 


			<br>
			<div class="body">
			<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0">
				<tr>
					<td bgcolor="silver" class="body">
						<a href="event_06.htm"><img border="1" src="img/events/6.gif" width="120" height="80" border="0" align="right" hspace="4" vspace="4"></a>
						<b><i>The Coronation of King Silvermoon</i></b><br>
						<i>8th May 2004</i><br>
<br>
Fortune has smiled up Prince Silvermoon, Keeper of the Ineffable Flame of Jurrawicca, Seeker the Ring of Poets.  By his hand was the evil orc chieftain Slagnost slain. In doing so, Prince Silvermoon has made good his claim to the Throne of Jurrawicca. As his Coronation draws near, folk from across the realm are clamouring to be invited, and to witness first-hand the fabled Lakeland of Jurawicca. 
