						<b><i>The Broken Circle</i></b><br>
						<i>3th-5th October 2003</i><br>
Once again the village of Berium-in-the-Swamp became an ampitheatre of valour, desperation, and tragedy. 
Deals were brokered, hearts were broken, and dark forces were pushed back for yet another day. 
An alliance was formed with local mages to protect the village, a dark ritual was interrupted in a tangled combat in the night, a King of Elves was crowned, famous heroes were drained of the last of their life under a glowing gaze, and finally the rebel Baron Mordikar was defeated in pitch battle at Berium Keep. 
The Trader's Guild blacklisted Berium as a result of mistreatment of their members in the village, and the King declared that all children under the age of 1 are to die, to defeat a shadowy spirit that is thought to have inhabited several infants.
<br>
Read the first issue of <a href="news_01.htm">The Mordavian Truth</a> for more news. <a href="event_04.htm">Click here for credits and reviews</a>.					
